cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Speech and Dialogue Processing (cs.SD) as it deals with speech enhancement. It also involves the use of deep neural networks (DNNs), which are commonly used in Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning (ML) research, making cs.CL and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves unsupervised learning, which falls under the sub-category of Statistical Learning (cs.SI). Finally, the use of a gating DNN to determine which expert is assigned to a given speech segment suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
